name: Yes, Virginia, There Is a Hercules
Genies and Grecians and Geeks, Oh My
For Those of You Just Joining Us

deck: Jack must fight against Aku's newest servants, the Ultra-robots.
name: Jack and the Ultra-robots

description:
Japanese title: Densetsu no Ysha ()

After winning a contest, twins Shugo and Rena enter The World as legendary hacker characters. Shugo is defeated by an unexpectedly powerful monster, which leads to his resurrection by a mysterious woman.
name: The Legendary Hero

description:
Japanese title: Kaito no Udewa ()

Balmung decides to throw an event to make cherry blossom trees bloom, which Shugo, Rena, and their new sidekick Mireille decide to attend. After a monster appears, Shugo must rely on a furry friend for help in battle.
name: Kite's Bracelet

description:
Japanese title: Fushich no Hane ()

Shugo levels up by letting the members in his party do all the work. Next, he helps another player whose sick grunty can only be cured with an item located in a dangerous part of The World.
name: The Phoenix Feather

description: After Robin swipes her cloak, Raven's leggy figure is revealed and she transforms into Lady Legasus; meanwhile Cyborg gets stuck in the discarded cloak, revealing a dark side of his personality.
name: Legs

description: Starfire convinces the reluctant Titans to try defeating their enemies with compassion rather than violence.
name: Breakfast Cheese

description: Cyborg and Beast Boy annoy the other Titans by refusing to say anything but "Waffles."
name: Waffles

description: Beast Boy invites Tara to the Titan's Valentine's Day dance and she accepts in order to destroy all of the Titans and exact revenge on Beast Boy.
name: Be Mine

description: Cyborg has a star-crossed crush on Jinx, the cutest member of The Hive.
name: Opposites

description: Robin tries to destroy some pesky mocking birds but they come back bigger, stronger, and ready to mock.
name: Birds

description: BB avoids being "the dumb one" by making the rest of the Titans dumber, which leaves only Silkie to save the day.
name: Brain Food

description: Robin goes undercover to destroy the Hive...right after he enjoys some of their perks.
name: In and Out

description: BB and Cyborg invite Starfire to join in their fun as long as she avoids dreaded uncle jokes.
name: Uncle Jokes

description: Robin tries to teach his superhero ways to Spanish speaking brothers Mas y Menos.
name: Mas Y Menos

description: A glimpse inside each Titan's dream world.
name: Dreams

description: Robin dabbles with magic, ignoring Raven's warning that he will anger the magic god.
name: Real Magic

description: When Robin gets frustrated with the Titans' disobedience he turns to...puppets.
name: Puppets, Whaaaaat?

description: After Starfire is set up by Blackfire and sent to prison, the Titans work to make Blackfire a better sister while Starfire plots her revenge.
name: Mr. Butt

description: Despite the Titans' protests, Beast Boy becomes convinced that replacing his body parts with robotic limbs makes him more manly.
name: Man Person

description: Aqualad asks Raven out on a date, which makes Beast Boy jealous. Cyborg tries to prove that Aqualad is really a pirate.
name: Pirates

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Shigatsu Tka)

Shido Itsuka is an ordinary high school student living with his little sister in Tengu City, a city that is often disrupted by "spatial quakes." During a spatial quake at the beginning of the school year, he meets a beautiful and mysterious "Spirit."
name: April 1X

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Sai-sekkin Sg)

Shido practices making women fall in love with him and has another encounter with the Spirit "Princess."
name: Another Close Encounter

description:
Proper Japanese Title: () (Sora Wakatsu Tsurugi)

With the support of Ratatoskr, Shido goes on a date with Tohka as Origami watches from afar.
name: For the Sky and the Sword

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Fukigen na Ame)

Shido encounters the mysterious "Hermit" one rainy day, and Tohka and Origami fight over Shido at school.
name: Sullen Rain

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Itetsuku Daichi)

Shido goes to Origami's apartment to look for Hermit's puppet, Yoshinon, who was lost during the last fight, and Tohka talks with Reine about her feelings for Shido.
name: Frozen Ground

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Koisuru Onsen)

Shido and the Spirits decide to visit Tengu City Hot Springs, but they run into some trouble on the way.
name: Romantic Hot Springs

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Raihsha-tachi)

A young AST joins Origami and the others in the fight against the Spirits. Meanwhile, another transfer student appears at Shido's school.
name: Visitors

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Sanj Kys Kyoku)

Shido takes Tohka, Kurumi, and Origami out on dates on the same day. Will he be found out?
name: Triple Capriccio

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Kyran no Akumu)

Shido and the others face off against "Nightmare," and they receive some unexpected help.
name: Frenzied Nightmare

description:
Proper Japanese Title: () (Hon no Seirei (Ifurto))

Shido learns the truth about his and Kotori's powers, and Origami reveals more details about her past.
name: Flame Spirit (Ifrit)

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Kauntodaun)

To get ready for his date with Kotori, Shido goes swimsuit shopping with Tohka and Yoshino. Meanwhile, Origami finds out more about Ifrit.
name: Countdown

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Yuzurenai Mono)

Shido and Kotori enjoy their date at the amusement park until they are interrupted by Origami.
name: That Which Cannot Be Forgiven

description: Proper Japanese Title: DATE TO DATE (Dto t Dto)
name: Date To Date

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Deir Raifu)

Shido and the Spirits are back, but Tohka's powers are unstable as she and Origami continue to compete for Shido's attention.
name: Daily Life

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Guf no miko)

Shido's class goes on a trip to DEM-affiliated Arubi Island, where he and Tohka get separated from the class and encounter twin Spirits.
name: Hurricane Children

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Futatsu no negai)

The tables are turned as Kaguya and Yuzuru try to make Shido fall in love with them.
name: Two Requests

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Kengen)

In the air, the Fraxinus is under attack while Kotori is away, and Shido and Tohka are being attacked on the ground while Kaguya and Yuzuru fight their last duel.
name: Manifestation

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Dva)

Shido meets Miku Izayoi, an idol also known as the Spirit, Diva, while getting ready for the joint cultural festival with other schools in Tengu City.
name: Diva

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Gruzu Myjikku)

The Tenou Festival begins, and Shido has to cross-dress to participate in the activities as Shiori to satisfy Miku.
name: Girls' Music

description:
Proper Japanese Title: () (Hagun Utahime (Gaburieru))

When the results of the first day of the Tenou Festival are announced, Miku decides she doesn't want to play by the rules anymore.
name: Gabriel

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Hatasubeki Yakusoku)

With Kurumi's help, Shido tries to convince Miku to join him in rescuing Tohka, and Miku has second thoughts about her stance on Shido.
name: The Promise to Keep

description: Proper Japanese Title: (Miku no shinjitsu)
name: The Truth About Miku

description: Proper Japanese Title: (Hanten)
name: Inversion
